edu.nyu.cs.addressbook

Class Contact

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.nyu.cs.addressbook.Contact
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Contact>, Iterable<ContactEntry>

    public class Contact
extends Object
implements Iterable<ContactEntry>, Comparable<Contact>
    Author:
    shenli

    The Contact class represents contact information.

    Contact object might be obtains by calls on ContactFactory.getContact(java.lang.String) factory methods which will return the Contact object.

    Contact objects are not constant; their values can be changed after they are created. Because Contact objects are implemented by synchronized list they can be shared.

      • getContacts

        public List<ContactEntry> getContacts()
        Returns an unmodifiable view of the contact list. This method allows modules to provide users with "read-only" access to internal lists. Query operations on the returned list "read through" to the specified list, and attempts to modify the returned list, whether direct or via its iterator, result in an UnsupportedOperationException.

        Returns:
        an unmodifiable view of the specified list. If no contact have been created, returns an empty list

      • add

        public void add(ContactEntry ce)
        Inserts the specified element at the specified position (lexicographical order) in this Contact list (optional operation). Shifts the element currently at that position (if any) and any subsequent elements to the right (adds one to their indices). The contact entry list will refuse to add null elements.

        Parameters:
        ce - element to be inserted

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Removes all of the elements from this Contact list (optional operation). The contact entry list will be empty after this call returns.

      • remove

        public boolean remove(ContactEntry ce)
        Removes the first occurrence of the specified element from this contact entry list, if it is present (optional operation).

        If this Contact list does not contain the element, it is unchanged. Returns true if this contact entry list contained the specified element (or equivalently, if this contact entry list changed as a result of the call).

        Parameters:
        ce - element to be removed from this contact entry list, if present
        Returns:
        true if this contact entry list contained the specified element

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this Contact for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also a Contact object, both objects have the same identifier.

        This implementation first checks if the specified object is this Contact. If so, it returns true; if not, it checks if the specified object is a Contact object. If not, it returns false; if so, it iterates over both Contact objects, comparing corresponding fields. If any comparison returns false, this method returns false. Otherwise it returns true when the iterations complete.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Contact c)
        Compares the contacts represented by two Contact objects. Returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this object is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified object.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface Comparable<Contact>
